Communication between the parent and child process?
What exactly is a docker daemon needed for?

Summary Checklist
To make space run debian echo "hello" work:

Map debian to a folder path (e.g., /images/debian/rootfs).

Set the PATH so the container knows where echo lives.

Implement a run sub-command in your main logic.

Add your binary to /usr/local/bin so you can drop the ./.
